cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image registration and proposes a new algorithm for the same. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses sparse approximations in parametric dictionaries, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper proposes a theoretical analysis of the registration algorithm and derives performance guarantees based on novel properties of redundant dictionaries. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for image registration and discusses its performance. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for image registration and discusses its theoretical analysis and performance guarantees.
